Class SubstitutableProperties

chav1961.purelib.basic.SubstitutableProperties
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,​java.lang.Object>
public class SubstitutableProperties
extends java.util.Properties

This class is an extension of the standard Properties class to support automatic substitutions and data type conversions when getting properties. Substitution as any template ${name} inside any property value. It substitutes with the value of other property, whose key is 'name'. You can also used one-level depth template ${${nameLocation}} whose 'nameLocation' means 'get key name to substitute from the nameLocation key'. All substitutions are recursive. A source of properties to substitute are own properties, but one-level depth template can be referenced to System.getProperties() key set. Maximum substitution depth level is restricted by 16

You can get property content not only as string, but a lot of other classes:

  • any appropriative Enum class constant
  • a subset of primitive type value (int, long, float, double, boolean)
  • a subset of wrappers to primitive type value (Integer, Long, Float, Double, Boolean)
  • a File or InputStream instance, if the property value contains valid file name
  • a URL or URI instance, if the property value contains valid URL or URI

To use it, simply type:

if (subst.getProperty("canUseSomething",boolean.class)) { final int amount = subst.getProperty("amountOfSomething",int.class); }

This class is thread-safe.
